 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}Bx]]></fr:tex> the identification type <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f=g]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001G.xml" title="n-truncated type" addr="//erct/erct-001G" type="local"><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n+1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:link> assuming the same for the identification types of each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Bx]]></fr:tex>. By <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0015.xml" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions" addr="//erct/erct-0015" type="local">Axiom <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-0015" /></fr:link>, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f=g]]></fr:tex> is a <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-0025.xml" title="Retract" addr="//erct/erct-0025" type="local">retract</fr:link> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
