 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}fx=gx]]></fr:tex> and the latter is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001G.xml" title="n-truncated type" addr="//erct/erct-001G" type="local"><html:span style="white-space: nowrap" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n+1]]></fr:tex>-truncated</html:span></fr:link> by our inductive hypothesis. Therefore, the result follows from <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-003S.xml" title="n-truncated types are closed under retracts" addr="//erct/erct-003S" type="local">Corollary <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-003S" /></fr:link>.</fr:p>
