   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>12</fr:month><fr:day>20</fr:day></fr:date><fr:anchor>6572</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="machine">//erct/unstable/438</fr:addr><fr:route>foreign-erct-unstable-438.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="" /><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B \colon  A \to  \mathsf {Type}]]></fr:tex> be a family of <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001I" type="local">propositions</fr:link>; fixing <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f : \mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{Bx}]]></fr:tex>, it suffices to show any other <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[g :\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}Bx]]></fr:tex> may be identified with <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>. As <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B]]></fr:tex> is a family of <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001I.xml" title="Proposition" addr="//erct/erct-001I" type="local">propositions</fr:link>, we know that each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Bx]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="//erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link> with centre <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[fx]]></fr:tex>. Therefore, the closure of <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="//erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link> types under dependent products (<fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001A.xml" title="Dependent product of contractible types" addr="//erct/erct-001A" type="local">Lemma <fr:contextual-number addr="//erct/erct-001A" /></fr:link>) shows that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathchoice {\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\textstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}{\scriptscriptstyle \prod _{
 \mathopen {}\left \lparen x:A\right \rparen \mathclose {}
}}Bx]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="foreign-erct-erct-001H.xml" title="Contractible type" addr="//erct/erct-001H" type="local">contractible</fr:link> with centre <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="foreign-erct-jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="//erct/jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
              <fr:month>12</fr:month>
